  <prompt>
    Create new shared library `Spaarke.Scheduling` at `src/server/shared/Spaarke.Scheduling/`. Net8.0, depends ONLY on `Spaarke.Core` + `Cronos` NuGet (~50KB) + standard `Microsoft.Extensions.*`. Add to `Spaarke.sln`. Reference from BFF API csproj.
    Source: spec.md FR-2.1, ADR-012 (new shared lib convention).
  </prompt>

  <goal>Empty `Spaarke.Scheduling.csproj` builds cleanly. Solution build succeeds. BFF references the lib. Cronos NuGet added with version pinned to latest stable v0.7.x.</goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared component library — new lib under `src/server/shared/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">In-process scheduling — no Azure Functions, no external scheduler</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">Adds ~50KB Cronos to BFF publish; verify within budget</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">Cronos has no HIGH CVE</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>shared-library-scaffolding</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
